- title_and_header = 'Accessibility statement for Drive in a Clean Air Zone'
- content_for(:title, title_and_header)

= link_to 'Return to the homepage', root_path, class: 'govuk-back-link'

%main.govuk-main-wrapper#main-content{role: 'main'}
  .govuk-grid-row
    .govuk-grid-column-two-thirds
      %h1.govuk-heading-xl
        = title_and_header
      %p
        This accessibility statement explains how accessible this service is, 
        what to do if you have difficulty using it, and how to report accessibility problems with the service.
      %p
        This service is part of the wider GOV.UK website. There is a separate 
        = link_to('accessibility statement',
                  'https://www.gov.uk/help/accessibility-statement',
                  id: 'gov-uk accessibility link')
        for the main GOV.UK website.
      
      %p
        This page only contains information about the Drive in a Clean Air Zone service.
      
      %h2.govuk-heading-m Using this service

      %p
        The Drive in a Clean Air Zone service allows users to check if 
        their vehicle meets emissions standards and if not pay the charge 
        liable in each Clean Air Zone. Payment is made through GOV Pay, 
        which has a separate 
        = succeed '.' do
          = link_to('accessibility statement',
                    'https://www.gov.uk/help/accessibility-statement',
                    id: 'gov-uk accessibility link') 
      %p
        This service is managed by the Joint Air Quality Unit (JAQU) supported 
        by the Department of Transport and Department for Environment, Food and 
        Rural Affairs. We want as many people as possible to be able to use this service.

      %p 
        This means you should be able to:
        %ul.govuk-list-govuk-list--bullet
          %li
            %p
              change colours, contrast levels and fonts
          %li
            %p
              zoom in up to 300% without the text spilling off the screen
          %li
            %p
              get from the start of the service to the end using just a keyboard
          %li
            %p
              get from the start of the service to the end using speech recognition software
          %li
            %p
              listen to most of the website using a screen reader (including the most recent
              versions of JAWS, NVDA and VoiceOver).
      %p We've also made the website text as simple as possible to understand.
      %p
        = link_to('AbilityNet',
                  'https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/',
                  id: 'ability-net-link')
        has advice on making your device easier to use if you have a disability.

      %h2.govuk-heading-m How accessible is this service?
      %p
        This service has been tested by the Digital Accessibility Centre (DAC) 
        and is fully compliant with the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines version 2.1 AA standard. 
      
      %h2.govuk-heading-m Technical information about this website's accessibility
      %p
        JAQU is committed to making its website accessible, in accordance with 
        the Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018.
      
      %p
        This website is fully compliant with the 
        = succeed '.' do
          = link_to('Web Content Accessibility Guidelines version 2.1 AA standard',
                    'https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/',
                    id: 'wcag21-guidelines-link')
      %h2.govuk-heading-m How we tested this service
      %p
        This service is tested at least monthly by the team that maintains it, and periodically by external bodies.  
        At the time of publishing, it was last tested externally by 
        = link_to('Digital Accessibility Centre Limited',
                  'https://www.digitalaccessibilitycentre.org/',
                  id: 'digital-accessibility-centre-link') 
        on the dates listed below.

      %table.govuk-table
        %thead.govuk-table__head
          %tr
            %th.govuk-table__header{scope: 'col'} Service
            %th.govuk-table__header{scope: 'col'} Date tested
        %tbody.govuk-table__body
          %tr.govuk-table__row
            %td.govuk-table__cell{scope: 'row'}
              Check if you will be charged
            %td.govuk-table__cell{scope: 'row'}
              26th November 2019
          %tr.govuk-table__row
            %td.govuk-table__cell{scope: 'row'}
              Pay a charge for a single vehicle
            %td.govuk-table__cell{scope: 'row'}
              25th March 2020
          %tr.govuk-table__row
            %td.govuk-table__cell{scope: 'row'}
              Business account for multiple vehicles
            %td.govuk-table__cell{scope: 'row'}
              30th March 2020

      %h2.govuk-heading-m What to do if you have difficulty using this service 
      %p
        If you have difficulty using this service, contact us by:
      %p
        Telephone: 0300 029 8888
        %br
        Monday to Friday, 10am to 4pm
        %br
        Find out about call charges
        %br
        = link_to('Online contact form',
                  'https://contact.dvla.gov.uk/caz',
                  id: 'contact-form-link')

      %h2.govuk-heading-m Reporting accessibility problems with this website
      %p
        We're always looking to improve the accessibility of this website. If you find any problems
        that are not listed on this page or think we're not meeting accessibility requirements,
        let us know using our
        = succeed '.' do
          = link_to('feedback form',
                    'https://contact.dvla.gov.uk/caz',
                    id: 'feedback-form-link')

      %h2.govuk-heading-m Enforcement procedure
      %p
        The Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC) is responsible for enforcing the Public
        Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018
        (the 'accessibility regulations'). If you're not happy with how we respond to your
        complaint,
        = succeed '.' do
          = link_to('contact the Equality Advisory and Support Service (EASS)',
                    'https://www.equalityadvisoryservice.com/',
                    id: 'eass-link')

      %p
        This statement was prepared on 8 July 2020.